<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-094-994  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 094 994.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Jan 22 1990 v11 n4 p18(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Xerox FormBase: makes forms and fills them. (Software Review)(Product Review) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Clayton, Chris; Price, Rebecca.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Xerox Desktop Software Div's FormBase generates forms and has abuilt-in database of information for insertion into the forms.andO;FormBase, $495, requires an IBM AT, PS/2 or compatible with640Kbytes of RAM, a mouse, an Enhanced Graphics Adapter displayand a hard disk.andP;  While FormBase is marketed primarily as a formsgenerator for businesses that must frequently revise theirinternal business forms, the addition of the database makes theprogram unique.andP;  New forms may be created graphically using amouse.andP;  Data that a field will accept can be limited.andP;  Designcapability is limited, but should suit most business needs.andO;FormBase uses Windows pull-down menus and dialogue boxes; mostprocesses can be easily mastered.andP;  The standard database isaccessed through blank forms.andP;  FormBase supports neither networksnor remote file servers; large offices or departments may findthat FormBase's database will not be useful.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Xerox Corp. Xerox Desktop Software Div. (products).andO;Ticker:    XRX.andO;Product:   FormBase (Forms generation software).andO;Topic:     Forms DesignFormsSoftware PackagesEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Specifications. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>